    <!-- Vulnerabilities Section -->
    <div class="news-item">
        <h2>🔥 Vulnerabilities</h2>

        <p>⚠️ <b>Weak Passwords on Solar Panels Pose Cybersecurity Risks</b><br>
        Hackers can **easily take control of solar installations** due to **factory-default and weak passwords**, threatening **grid security**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/03/hackers-can-attack-your-rooftop-solar.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🛑 <b>Elastic Patches Critical Kibana Prototype Pollution Vulnerability (CVE-2025-25012)</b><br>
        The flaw could enable **remote code execution** in **Kibana 8.15.0 - 8.17.3**. Immediate update recommended.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/174999/security/elastic-kibana-critical-flaw.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>📌 <b>Over 1,000 WordPress Sites Infected With JavaScript-Based Attack</b><br>
        Attackers inject **multiple backdoors**, modify wp-config.php, and add **malicious SSH keys** to maintain persistence.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2025/03/over-1000-wordpress-sites-infected-with.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🔴 <b>EncryptHub Deploys New Malware & Ransomware via Phishing</b><br>
        The **EncryptRAT** malware enables **remote command execution, data theft, and system takeover**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2025/03/encrypthub-deploys-ransomware-and.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    </div>

    <!-- Adversaries Section -->
    <div class="news-item">
        <h2>🕵️ Adversaries & Attacks</h2>

        <p>📡 <b>Akira Ransomware Uses Unsecured Webcam to Bypass EDR & Encrypt Network</b><br>
        Attackers **gained access via IoT webcam**, mounted SMB shares, and launched ransomware.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/akira-ransomware-encrypted-network-from-a-webcam-to-bypass-edr/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>💰 <b>Python Malware on PyPI Steals Ethereum Wallets</b><br>
        The **set-utils** package intercepted **private keys** using the **Polygon blockchain** for exfiltration.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/ethereum-private-key-stealer-on-pypi-downloaded-over-1-000-times/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>🔍 <b>Typosquatting Malware Targets Linux & macOS Go Developers</b><br>
        Attackers **published deceptive Go libraries** with **remote execution functions** targeting **finance sector developers**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://hackread.com/malware-infects-linux-macos-typosquatted-go-packages/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>📊 <b>Cisco Talos Uncovers Large-Scale Attack on Japanese Organizations</b><br>
        Attackers exploited **CVE-2024-4577** and deployed **TaoWu plugins, Mimikatz, and Alibaba Cloud-based payloads**.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://www.infosecurity-magazine.com/news/attackers-japan-cobalt-strike/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

        <p>💻 <b>New Browser Extension Malware Spoofs Password Managers</b><br>
        Polymorphic extensions **mimic trusted security tools**, tricking users into exposing credentials.</p>
        <p>🔗 <a href="https://hackread.com/squarex-unveils-polymorphic-extensions-that-morph-infostealers-into-any-browser-extension-password-managers-wallets-at-risk/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
